title: For Sale:  SIG 556 in OD Green
postcontent:
Gonna miss this rifle, it was my first 5.56mm rifle and I did quite a few modifications to it.

Ok, starting with the round count looking at around 600. Really not a whole lot considering the years I've had it. Never ever fired cheap rounds (i.e: Wolf) only M855.

The rifle was one of the original "SWAT" models SIG first put out. However, I didn't care much for the Samson quad rail which made this rifle really front heavy and unbalanced.

To reduce the front weight I replaced the quad handguard rail with some Swiss polymer handguards. Because the gas system still made the front a little heavy I replaced the buttstock with something heavier, a magpul UBR. Although not needed because of the way the rifle works I put in a Wolf Tungten buffer tube inside the UBR buttstock (no maximize space and weight balance) What happened was a great weight rebalance with the rifle.

I added some other things to the rifle, including a Griffin charging handle which is canted downwards instead of upwards (so your hand isn't being obstructed by an optic), installed SIG Diopter iron sights and I have an aluminium strike plate installed on the UBR buttstock. Also installed the new top rail.

title: For Sale:  Ruger M77 Mark II 7mm Rem  -- Beautiful and Pristine!
postcontent:
This Ruger M77 Mark II 7mm Rem Mag is an extremely beautiful as well as functional piece to add to your collection.  While I don't have the box, it is in NIB PRISTINE CONDITION and to the best of my knowledge has never been fired.  

It sports the stainless steel barrel and fixtures with the black laminate stock but appears as a deep forest/mossy green hardwood grained stock.

This model is of the second gen. M77 line which was retooled almost entirely and reintroduced in 1991 as the Mark II. The safety, bolt, and trigger were completely redesigned. The claw extractor was retained, but the bolt face was opened up to allow controlled-round feeding. And that is to name just a few major modifications to the original M77.  This line is now out of production as of 2006.  This rifle was build in 1996 according to its SN, yet remains in brand new condition!

Included in the purchase of this amazingly accurate rifle is a heavy leather  shoulder strap, a Bushnell Sportview 3X-9X/32 scope, trigger guard (lost key but easy to open without it), and a hard plastic carrying/storage case. 

Link to User Manual:                                                                    https://ruger-docs.s3.amazonaws.com/_manuals/m77MarkII.pdf

Beautiful Smith & Wesson Model 5906 9MM all stainless semi-auto. Includes 2 factory mags, 15 and 10 round. I would rate this a 9.75 out of 10. Has a 4 inch barrel. Novac 3 dot sights. Ambidextrous safety/decocker.  It has no significant defect....one of the finest 5906's I have seen. 

FTF/W ID MUST BE 21.
If out of state, can be shipped to your FFL for $25.
$435 Firm
